Package: IfamazonratingsReliable
Type: Package
Title: Examinating if Amazon's product ratings are reliable based on reviews analysing
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("QA", "Nguyen", email = "anhmilan@gmail.com",
                  role = c("aut", "cre"))
Maintainer: Nguyen QA <anhmilan@gmail.com>
Description: This packge is used to check if average Amazon rating of each product is reliable. 
    Reviews from buyers will be sentimental analysed using library "bing" by Bing Liu. 
    If the number of negative words is greater than 40% of total sentimental words, the product is considered as having got a BAD reviews and vice versa.
License: GPL-3
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0),dplyr
Imports: rvest, tidytext, tidyverse,gsubfn,magrittr
RoxygenNote: 7.0.2
